description:
The investigative judgement. This doctrine has become the subject of much debate lately. What we believe about this issue directly affects our eternal life. It will determine your understanding of the very plan of salvation. 

Lately, a battle has been brewing over the investigative judgement. Many are questioning this doctrine, as it seems to conflict with their view of salvation. 

In this video, we will go straight to the Bible to answer 10 key questions about the Investigative judgment, including "Is the judgment even Biblical?", "Was the atonement completed at the cross?", "What is Jesus doing in Heaven right now?", "Can we have assurance of Salvation?", "Can we have complete and total victory over sin?", "Where will the judgment take place, and when?", "How will be be judged?", and more! Friends, you don't want to miss this powerful video that deals with subject matter of eternal consequence! May God lead and guide you as you watch!

0:00 Battle of the Gospels
3:13 Is the Judgment Biblical?
10:53 Who will be judged?
11:35 What will be judged?
13:21 Where will the judgment take place?
14:02 When will the judgment take place?
15:40 Why does their need to be a judgment?
19:05 Was the Atonement completed at the cross?
22:32 What is Jesus doing in Heaven right now?
23:24 Can we have assurance of salvation?
25:15 Can we have total victory over sin?
29:23 Jesus Christ - the Hero of the judgment
